main event: A civilian observed an unidentified object in the sky for about 15-30 seconds in Eugene, Oregon on July 25, 1966.
interesting points: The observation took place during the day with clear weather conditions and the sun shining on the object., The object was described as too far away to distinguish its shape, but it appeared to be on a straight flight path., The observer noted a lack of sound from the object, stating it seemed quiet with no noticeable sound., There is a mention of a triangular object seen near the airport on the same date, which appeared to have landing gear., The report concluded that the sighting was possibly an aircraft based on the description given.
witness description: civilian observer who reported the sighting
